TITLE: Configuring Computed Property Mapping in AutoMapper
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to configure mapping for a computed fullName property using forMember() function. The fullName is derived by concatenating firstName and lastName.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nartc/mapper/blob/main/packages/documentations/docs/tutorial/mapping-configurations.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { createMap, forMember, mapFrom } from '@automapper/core';

createMap(
    mapper,
    User,
    UserDto,
    forMember(
        (destination) => destination.fullName,
        mapFrom((source) => source.firstName + ' ' + source.lastName)
    )
);
```

