TITLE: Using MapperPickType in TypeScript with AutoMapper
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use MapperPickType to create a new class that only includes selected properties from an original class. This example picks 'foo' and 'bar' properties while excluding 'baz'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nartc/mapper/blob/main/packages/classes/mapped-types/src/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
class Foo {
    @AutoMap()
    foo!: string;
    @AutoMap()
    bar!: number;
    @AutoMap()
    baz!: boolean;
}

class PickFooBar extends MapperPickType(Foo, ['foo', 'bar']) {}

createMap(mapper, Foo, PickFooBar);

const foo = new Foo();
foo.foo = 'foo';
foo.bar = 123;
foo.baz = true;

const pickedFooBar = mapper.map(foo, Foo, PickFooBar);
console.log(pickedFooBar);
/**
 * PickFooBar { foo: 'foo', bar: 123 }
 * only foo and bar have been picked
 */
```

