TITLE: Using MapperIntersectionType in TypeScript with AutoMapper
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates MapperIntersectionType which creates a new class combining properties from two parent classes. The example shows mapping from the intersection class to each of the original classes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nartc/mapper/blob/main/packages/classes/mapped-types/src/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
class Foo {
    @AutoMap()
    foo!: string;
}

class Bar {
    @AutoMap()
    bar!: number;
}

class IntersectFooBar extends MapperIntersectionType(Foo, Bar) {}

createMap(mapper, IntersectFooBar, Foo);
createMap(mapper, IntersectFooBar, Bar);

const intersect = new IntersectFooBar();
intersect.foo = 'foo';
intersect.bar = 123;

const foo = mapper.map(intersect, IntersectFooBar, Foo);
console.log(foo);
/**
 * Foo { foo: 'foo' }
 */

const bar = mapper.map(intersect, IntersectFooBar, Bar);
console.log(bar);
/**
 * Bar { bar: 123 }
 */
```

