TITLE: Implementing Value Resolver for Tax Calculation in TypeScript AutoMapper
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to implement a Resolver for calculating tax based on item type and price, then using it with mapFrom() in a mapping configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nartc/mapper/blob/main/packages/documentations/docs/mapping-configuration/for-member/map-from.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export const taxResolver: Resolver<Item, ItemDto, number> = {
    resolve(item): number {
        return item.type === 'A' ? item.price * 0.5 : item.price * 0.9;
    },
};

createMap(
    mapper,
    Item,
    ItemDto,
    forMember((d) => d.tax, mapFrom(taxResolver))
);
```

